If you don't share enough, such as just saying "Hi!", you are less likely to get a response.
If you share too much, such as "I have issues with my mother" -- -- the request is also less likely to be accepted.
So there is an optimal level of openness, for example, "Great artworks in your apartment! I'm on vacation with my family."
How can one achieve this level of openness with design?
We use the size of the text field to recommend the right amount of text. We also provide tips on what topics to write about.
Our entire company is built on the hope that the right design can help us overcome our prejudices towards strangers.
